FBIS4-66146 "drweu104aa_94012" FBIS-WEU-94-104 Daily Report 26 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Hungary's Jeszenszky: Paris Talks Must Involve Minority Hungary's Jeszenszky: Paris Talks Must Involve Minority LD2605180894 Budapest MTV Television Network in Hungarian 1700 GMT 26 May 94 LD2605180894 Budapest MTV Television Network Hungarian BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Jeszenszky stated that representatives of the Hungarians of Slovakia and Romania must also be involved in the preparatory discussions of the Paris conference on stability in Europe. His comments came at his address to the conference. Jeszenszky said: the Hungarian delegation will be formulating a separate opinion in the form of an explanatory declaration, which will call attention to the fact that the three million Hungarians living outside Hungary are not represented by anyone at the Paris talks.
